        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 6:29PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 629 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Ellenton, or near Aiken Mall, moving west at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Aiken, North Augusta, Clearwater, Aiken Mall, Belvedere, New
Ellenton, Jackson, Gloverville, Burnettown, Audubon's Silver Bluff
Sanctuary, Savannah River Site Badge Office, Redcliffe Plantation
State Historic Site, and Boyd Pond Park.

This includes Interstate 520 in South Carolina between mile markers
20 and 21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
